Oppo’s next flagship smartphone — the Find X5 Pro — will have a Qualcomm Snapdragon 8 Gen 1 processor and up to 12GB of RAM, according to a leak from WinFuture. The Snapdragon 8 Gen 1 was released in November 2021, and it is claimed to be the world’s fastest smartphone chip. The Find X5 Pro will also feature an Adreno 730 graphics chip, a 3,216 x 1,440-pixel display with a 120Hz refresh rate, and 256GB of internal storage. Its 1440p resolution will be packed into a 6.7-inch AMOLED display. The smartphone has a 30MP front camera and a triple rear camera system with a 50MP primary lens, a 50MP wide-angle lens, and a 13MP telephoto camera. Oppo is powering the cameras with its in-house neural processing unit — the MariSilicon X. In terms of battery life, WinFuture said the Find X5 Pro could pack a 5,000 mAh battery and 80W fast charging capabilities. WinFuture predicts the launch price to be approximately €1,200 (R21,200) and according to The Verge, it is expected to first release in Europe.